The paper focuses on Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves reasoning with visual content and language. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a structured visual representation - scene graph, and a Scene Graph Convolutional Network (SceneGCN) to reason over it. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
